snippet.textDisplay:
Nothing beats the Sufi poetry and nuances! Salute to all the creative, passionate pakistani artists who have understood the legacy and have always spread the word.

A huge shout out to the legends who belong to garhana's and qawalls across the neighbourhood. The art emerged from the same land, we both have its imprint but pakistan kept the art alive. 

Bless you and much love from an avid listener of Sir Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan.

snippet.textDisplay:
Translation-
anslation
You've taken away my looks, my identity, by just a glance.
By making me drink the wine of love-potion,
You've intoxicated me by just a glance;
My fair, delicate wrists with green bangles in them,
Have been held tightly by you with just a glance.
I give my life to you, Oh my cloth-dyer,
You've dyed me in yourself, by just a glance.
I give my whole life to you Oh, Nijam,
You've made me your bride, by just a glance.
